race.comment: FLYING ARGYLE (1) got a long way back and couldn't get involved last start in a BM74 over 1400m at Scone. Better placed back to this distance and finds a far easier race. Freshened up and should be ready to run well with the help of a nice gate. SEND A TELEGRAM (8) led in a change of tactics last time out and got the cash in a maiden here at today's distance. Took a while to break the ice but can go on with it now. EDGE OF MIDNIGHT (5) has been in the top four at all five runs this prep, the latest effort an eye-catching third over 1100m here. Genuine gelding who will be thereabouts again with a lovely run assured out of gate one. EXTERNUS (2) settled midfield and failed to get involved when resuming over 1000m at Canberra recently. Can improve over the extra furlong today. LAST DRUID (4) is another who can do better dropping back from provincial racing.
